The course teaches how to apply the concepts of psychology of religion for analyzing of different cases. First, the overview of the method of case analysis is presented. Second every student chooses an case to be analyzed. Third, the theoretical concept and practical method of analyze will be chosen. The course ends with presentation of research projects.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The ability to use case study method on the field of psychology of religion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. Knows the case study method. 2. Is able to determine the case (person, event, institution, process) as the research object. 3. Can create on base of a concept of the psychology of religion a case analyze model and apply this model.
